answers.answer: Could be baby up against them. my little guy likea to do that. Could be your rib cage expanding some too.

I'm no Dr but they say if you have upper right quadrant pain it could be a sign of preeclampsia. How's your blood pressure? Headaches? If all that is fine its prob just baby is in a weird position. Spinning babies website has a lot of good info

It could be baby kicking you in the ribs or laying there. Also he or she is might be head down in position. My little girl is head down and I actually feel her foot hit my rib leave it there and move it out.

I had mild preeclampsia but it has passed I haven't had headaches and blood pressure is fine. It eases if I go on all fours (my dog looked at me very weird doing this) I've read that it's the uterus expanding and it happens around 35/36 weeks, I'm alright today. Thanks anyway was very painful last night. X
